## Performance Strategy by Phase

### Phase 1-2 (< 1M rows)
- Standard B-tree indexes on date + FK columns
- Connection pooling via PgBouncer

### Phase 3+ (1M-50M rows)
- Materialized views for org/BU/division aggregations
- Partition fact_revenue by year: `PARTITION BY RANGE (revenue_date)`
- Redis query result cache (TTL: 5 min for live, 1 hr for historical)

### Phase 7 — Customer revenue operations & workbook I/O

Phase 7 is **additive** on Phases 1–6. Before migrations or new tables for **variance cases**, **customer common name**, **notification/deep links**, or **template-versioned** Excel profiles:

1. Read [`docs/architecture/phase-7-changes.md`](../../docs/architecture/phase-7-changes.md), [`docs/architecture/phase-7-implementation-handoff.md`](../../docs/architecture/phase-7-implementation-handoff.md), and [`docs/requirements/phase-7-requirements.md`](../../docs/requirements/phase-7-requirements.md).
2. Align import behavior with **reference** [`samples/EUROPE_Weekly Commercial Dashboard.xlsx`](../../samples/EUROPE_Weekly%20Commercial%20Dashboard.xlsx) (`Sheet1` primary for v1); **ingest value rows only** for facts — **skip** paired delta rows in v1 (see handoff decision D2).
3. Preserve **backward compatibility** for existing `dim_customer` / `fact_revenue` rows (prefer **additive** columns and Alembic backfills). Implemented schema uses **`tenant_id`** on dimensions/facts — Phase 7 tables must match.

